               <t:note>
                  <t:date type="foundation" notBefore="1400" notAfter="1500">1400-1500</t:date>
                  <t:desc type="foundation">Local tradition tells that the rock-hewn church is ancient foundation; it was re-established in the time of King Yosṭos (r. <t:date>1711-1716</t:date>) and <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">King Yoḥannǝs IV</t:persName> (r. <t:date>1872-1889</t:date>).</t:desc>
                  <t:ab type="history">Gadām. The monastic community declined, only a few monks reside at the church.  
</t:ab>
                  <t:ab type="description">
                     <t:figure>
                        <t:graphic url="Sites/BHM.tif">
                           <t:desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</t:desc>
                        </t:graphic>
                     </t:figure>9 Mss. photographed: <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESbhm001">BHM-001</t:ref> “Four Gospels”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESbhm002">BHM-002</t:ref> “Miracles of Mary”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESbhm003">BHM-003</t:ref> “Homiliany for the feasts of St. Michael; Miracles of Michael f. 59R; Homily of the 24 Heavenly Priests”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESbhm004">BHM-004</t:ref> “Missal”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESbhm005">BHM-005</t:ref> “Homily of Mary”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESbhm006">BHM-006</t:ref> “Synaxarium (second part)”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESbhm007">BHM-007</t:ref> “Synaxarium (The first half of the year)”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESbhm008">BHM-008</t:ref> “Collection of Images ”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESbhm009">BHM-009</t:ref> “Book of the Baptismal Rite”.</t:ab>
           
